1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper discusses classical visibility-based exploration methods from computational geometry and presents algorithmic results for an important algorithmic problem that combines stationary art gallery-type aspects with watchman-type issues in an online scenario. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the use of autonomous robots with scanning capabilities and presents a competitive strategy for exploring polygonal regions. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses the use of laser scanning for surveying the environment and explores the problem of exploring polygonal regions with time discrete vision. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents algorithmic results for an important algorithmic problem and discusses the use of competitive strategies for exploring polygonal regions. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of autonomous robots and presents a competitive strategy for exploring polygonal regions, which can be seen as an application of AI in robotics.
